[normal]Role of Community
[normal] Activities Program
[normal]8
[normal]. 
[normal]In order to widen its impact 
[normal]beyond the school setting
[normal], HIH is 
[normal]also designing and implementing community building events in the five locations in which it currently has schools. The 
[normal]goals of this Shared Communities Program are: to establish a wide range of Jewish-Arab community activities, from sports and culture to dialogue, study and responding to discriminatory events, and open the community activity to all who are interested.  In new locations the communities play a central role in helping open new schools. 
[normal]9
[normal]. 
[normal]As of March 2012 HIH had 3 bilingual schools in Jerusalem, Wadi Ara, and the Galilee. Thanks to three-year core funding from the United States gover
[normal]nment’s U.S. Agency for International Development and with matching funds, 
[normal]HIH
[normal] 
[normal]launched its
[normal] Shared Community Project
[normal]. The goal of this project is 
[normal]to establish community leadership and structures
[normal], and develop 
[normal]a range of 
[normal]vibrant 
[normal]community
[normal] 
[normal]activities (from sports, culture, family activities and excursions, to dialogue groups, language study, and responding to 
[normal]discriminatory
[normal] 
[normal]events)
[normal] 
[normal]t
[normal]hat will
[normal] create 
[normal]a civic infrastructure for social inclusion and civic equality 
[normal]beyond the wa
[normal]lls of the school
[normal].  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]10
[normal]. 
[normal]In March 2012 
[normal]HIH selected Jaffa and Haifa as its two new communities
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]The Shared Community Project 
[normal]staff 
[normal]develop
[normal]ed
[normal] local leadership
[normal] and together 
[normal]they 
[normal]design
[normal]ed
[normal] activities to fit the needs and interests of the Jewish and Arab populations
[normal] in these communities
[normal]. Parents 
[normal]and children 
[normal]participated in cultural events, holiday celebrations, 
[normal]and community gardening
[normal]; 
[normal]adults 
[normal]enrolled in Arab and Hebrew language classes
[normal], pa
[normal]rticipated in dialogue sessions, and played on 
[normal]integrated 
[normal]basketball teams
[normal]. They got to know one another and formed friendships. As a result of these interactions, the Jaffa and Haifa communities strengthened the bonds between Jews and Arabs, enabling them
[normal] to cooperate and open a bilingual pre-kindergarten in each of their 
[normal]communities in September 2013 with an equal number of Jewish and Arab children
[normal] enrolled and with hundreds on waiting lists
[normal].
[normal]1
[normal]1
[normal]. 
[normal]The community organizers will continue to develop and run 
[normal]local activities
[normal] for the more veteran communities to insure strong parental involvement, a growing student body
[normal],
[normal] and joint Jewish and Arab communal life. They will 
[normal]help insure that the new bilingual schools in Jaffa and Haifa 
[normal]continue to grow with 
[normal]another 
[normal]grade each year, 
[normal]and will continue to develop and maintain relationships with the Municipality and the Ministry of Education.
[normal] They will also help start new communities and new schools.
