[normal]Country-Wide 
[normal]Community 
[normal]Event
[normal]1
[normal]2
[normal]. 
[normal]Community 
[normal]o
[normal]rganizers are also responsible 
[normal]for 
[normal]organiz
[normal]ing
[normal] an annual event
[normal],
[normal] bringing together the Hand in Hand communities from all around the country.  
[normal]HIH
[normal] piloted a country-wide 
[normal]event 
[normal]around Ramadan 
[normal]for the first time in July 20
[normal]13 
[normal]and it was a huge success. HIH
[normal] expected 250 people
[normal], but 
[normal]closed registration with 650 
[normal]Arabs and Jews
[normal] 
[normal]com
[normal]ing from all over the country. 
[normal]The program included a public discussion with a Rabbi, a Sheikh and a Priest about the notion of fasting and forgiving in the three religions as well as musical performances. Bringing community leaders together for the planning of such an event empowers th
[normal]em as they realize that they are part of something much bigger than their own community. They are able 
[normal]to share stories of success and failure and learn from each other’s experiences. 
