[normal]Publicizing HIH’s Success
[normal]es
[normal]1
[normal]3
[normal]. 
[normal]While our bi
[normal]lingual schools and shared communities demonstrate that it is possible for Jews and Arabs to peacefully coexist, interact, and become friends, the experience of cooperation that we have demonstrated will have a limited impact if it remains known only to th
[normal]ose who have personally experienced it. Therefore, HIH has hired an 
[normal]Organizational Journalist
[normal] to join the team, and help publicize our story of an inclusive society to as wide an audience as possible
[normal] in Hebrew, English and Arabic
[normal].  HIH’s “doing” in the bil
[normal]ingual schools and in the shared communities will inform the telling
[normal], which will illustrate the viability of inclusion, shared society and equality.  
[normal]This will counter 
[normal]the 
[normal] feelings
[normal] of helplessness and despair that exists in no small part because of the media’s highlighting negative stories. Our stories 
[normal]that appear in radio segments, television reports, in the Israeli and international press, 
[normal]and on Facebook 
[normal]https://www.facebook.com/HandinHandil
[normal] 
[normal]provide a powerful message that a different reality is possible 
[normal]in 
[normal]Israel
[normal].
